{"cursor":"7568","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\nThe 'Puerta del Sol' (Spanish for \"Gate of the Sun\") is one of the best known\nand busiest places in Madrid. This is the centre ([[Kilometre Zero|Km 0]]) of\nthe radial network of Spanish roads. The square also contains the famous clock\nwhose bells mark the traditional eating of the Twelve Grapes and the beginning\nof a new year. The New Year's celebration has been broadcast live on La 1 since\nDecember 31, 1962.\n","linknr":179,"url":"Puerta_del_Sol","recorded":1374778880,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Puerta_del_Sol&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Puerta_del_Sol&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/File:Tragabolas_en_la_Puerta_del_Sol.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/98/Tragabolas_en_la_Puerta_del_Sol.jpg/277px-Tragabolas_en_la_Puerta_del_Sol.jpg","/wiki/File:Tragabolas_en_la_Puerta_del_Sol.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.22wmf8/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","/wiki/Madrid","/wiki/Kilometre_Zero","/wiki/Transportation_in_Spain","/wiki/Twelve_Grapes","/wiki/Televisi%C3%B3n_Espa%C3%B1ola","#History","#Famous_buildings_and_landmarks","#Location_in_Madrid","#Namesakes","#External_links","/w/